verse.lines:
{lang-eng}There is a way that leads to life;
The few that find it never die.
Past mountain peaks graced white with snow;
The way grows brighter as it goes.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}The river runs beside the road,
It’s waters living as they flow.
In liquid voice the water calls;
On thirsty knees a pilgrim falls.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Sometimes it’s good to look back down;
We’ve come so far, we’ve gained such ground.
But joy is not in where we’ve been.
Joy is Who’s waiting at the end.{/lang-eng}
